Title: Brand New Schwinn Falcon 20" Kids' Bike Blue #65SF1
text: Brand new, still in the box. Asking $130.  Highlights Kids bike featuring a durable steel frame, perfect for riding around the neighborhood 20-inch wheel fits riders ages 7 to 13, or 48 ‚Äì 60 inches tall SmartStart design features a durable steel frame and kid-specific proportions for easier pedaling and handling. Includes both rear coaster break and front caliper brake; easing the transition to a bigger, hand-brake-only bike when they‚Äôre ready Single speed drivetrain is easy to use Tool-free adjustable seat post allows the bike to grow with your child as they get taller Description  Riding is a blast with the Falcon kids bike by Schwinn. This bike features a durable steel frame with Smart Start geometry, which has been carefully calibrated to a child‚Äôs proportions for a comfortable, confident ride. This includes a lighter bike frame for added control, smaller grip handles to match smaller hands, and a narrower pedal position to match narrow kid hips. Rear coaster and front hand brakes ease the transition to a bigger, hand-brake-only bike when they‚Äôre ready. Plus, the tool-free adjustable seat post easily accommodates your child as they grow. Like all Schwinn bikes, the Falcon includes a limited lifetime warranty for as long as you own the bike. Tons of fun is just a pedal away with the Falcon. Enjoy the freedom of riding a Schwinn. Title: Think Grow LED Horticulture Grow lights! Commercial grade! New Cond.!
text: Hello Craigslist!!    I have for Sale some 'ThinkGrow' LED Model-W Grow lights. Fully dimmable and full spectrum. If you're looking at this ad, you should know that these are the Ferrari of grow lights. They are in AMAZING condition and work perfectly. No issues whatsoever.   ...keeping it short and sweet, They are 1000 Watt Equivalent using only 630 Real Watts. Commercial grade. Extremely efficient, FULL spectrum. Google them for yourself for full specs because its too much to get into here. All you need to know is these are the best of the best. Perfect for cannabis, indoor gardening, micro-green farming, growing your own fruits and veggies indoors. Any type of agriculture cultivation really.   They are able to be ran in configuration with one another or individually using a Trolmaster controller. You can run them without the controller and just plug them into a regular 120v outlet. Ill include the adapter for you. These are the cream of the crop of horticulture lights. Super easy to use.  THESE CAN BE RAN IN EITHER VEG OR FLOWER.  The light bars are removable.   VEG IT COVERS A 7X7 SQUARE FOOT GROW SPACE EACH LIGHT  FLOWER IT COVERS A 5X5 SQUARE FOOT GROW SPACE EACH LIGHT  They normally run $1300+ each IF you can find them. I'll do $1000 each. In the pictures they are at 1% power just to give you and idea, at 100% they are absolutely insane. At 100% power they are as powerful and bright as a 1000W has yet they only use 630 WATTS!  Everybody is worried about density with LED and it is absolutely there. These are full spectrum and more efficient then a HPS. Full spectrum = more purple and more flavor! LED is the future, look at all the big facilities transitioning to LED. Equivalent yields and quality and nearly half the electricity cost.   If you buy MORE then 2 I'll do $900 each. I have 6 left. May be interested in trades for quads? dirt bikes? No more equipment. I have other items if interested. AC units, c02 tanks etc. Flood tables, Everything you need.

Title: BMW R1100GS w/ABS 3700 OBO
text: 1995 BMW R1100GS with ABS $3700 OBO.   Renewed Reg May 2023 Photos taken 04/20/2022.  Bike starts and runs, doesnt smoke under hard acceleration and makes decent power. Compression is fine. Can do a wheelie if you want and go 120mph, but realize it weighs 600lbs. She's a road warrior, not a BMX bike.   No tire kickers and garage princess folks. She's my little Rocinante Panzer Princess. Hopefully you are a person that understands why the BMW community loves this bike so much. I even got the Lenny Rocket Sprockets if you wanna install them in the future.  If you read everything below, this price is a steal (ill even say I sold it to you for $100).  If you know your way around a bike, especially BMW maintenance, you'll realize why this is a gem of a buy for you. Turnkey ready, mechanically sound, new fluids, pads, filters, fuses, solid tires, bright LEDs, new clutch, new upgraded metal head gaskets and new valve cover seals, new fuel injectors, heads recently serviced and timing set. You literally don't need to do anything but ride it. I'm forthcoming about anything on it, so just ask.   Bikes require regular maintenance, and usually only BMW mechanics will work on BMW bikes. So you either give them your arm and leg, or you do it all yourself. If you read below, I've shown you how easy it is to do yourself with detailed resources/videos/manuals/guides/schematics with detailed part numbers and more.  Please be a serious buyer and communicate with me to set a date to see it. I'm in the AG/Grover/Pismo area. Too many flakey people lately.    259 (R 850 GS, R 1100 GS) BMW R 1100 GS. Type Code: 0409 Produced 05/1994  This is all the info you will ever need for parts on this bike Ebay, Amazon, wherever. Schematics for all the parts and part numbers here: RealOEM.com. They have detailed photographs sectioned out for each part of the bike with part numbers as well as their compatibility with parts on newer models. My PDF manual, type a keyword and find the maintenance piece you need broken down in elaborate detail.   I love this bike immensely. Can carry a lot of stuff, great on mileage, handles beautifully. She‚Äôs like the hot girlfriend everyone can‚Äôt stop staring at. Loud guttural poppy engine, not meant for hauling ass like on a sport bike but great for all around travel (yes she can do a wheelie, but shes also like 500-600lbs). Regular compliments and stoke from enthusiasts all around. She is truly a tough and beautiful panzer. I am sad to see her go, but I need the money and have a truck already. I just hope you enjoy it as much as I have and give her the love I wish I could. Clean title in hand.  Mechanic owned, regular maintenance done and can provide you the mileage/photos/receipts of when it was all done so you can keep track too. She's got some paint flakes, scratches, etc, but she's Rocinante, total work horse.  Lot's of amazing spare parts, bolts, tools, and other useful stuff included below. I am going to be super thorough in here because I like selling things better than when I found them. Brake fluid, brake pads, and oil serviced less than 1k miles ago. All the mission critical stuff on it is pretty new so you don't have to do much other than oil changes.  $3700 OBO, cash-in-hand to ride. Read the whole listing here because there's a lot of awesome stuff I'm giving ya. Know this bike down to every nut and bolt, been riding BMW's for 10 years now.   Valid license and/or M1 License required (usually I'll take a photo of your license and you can have a friend with you stay with me while you ride it), I have a spare helmet and jacket if needed. If you drop it, you buy it although it has caging around the valve covers so it wouldn't be much of a big deal. I can ride to you or you can meet me somewhere in the area.   Perks  ‚Ä¢ Lots of key maintenance done and an entirely new clutch, she is looking for new adventures, still room for other fun projects. ‚Ä¢ Paper manual with photos and easily searchable pdf manual with drawn schematics included. ‚Ä¢ Tags recently renewed in CA. Good til May 2022. Insurance is $15 a month, it is amazing. Clean title in hand  ‚Ä¢ Nice adjustable windscreen ‚Ä¢ Digital Oil Temp, Gear Position, and Fuel Level Readouts ‚Ä¢ ABS system for safe breaking ‚Ä¢ Super Bright White LED lights ‚Ä¢ Cell phone mount for GPS ‚Ä¢ Passenger Seat Included ‚Ä¢ PIAA Fog Lights (helps a lot when you are out in the country) ‚Ä¢ Side/Back Carrying Cases with locks and keys with black reflector tape. You can fit an amazing amount of things in the cases and back of the bike with ropes/bunjee chords. Just did a big sur run with like 300lbs on it.  ‚Ä¢ Engine cage oilpan/protector and highway footrests ‚Ä¢ I have Lennie‚Äôs Rocket Sprockets but have not installed them yet ($250 shipped from AUS). Supposed to help with torque all around. Also helps with the slow torque response at higher speeds/RPM‚Äôs and gears. ‚Ä¢ SPARE set of cleaned cylinder heads/pushrods/rockers/valves/springs/camshafts/new valve stem seals, etc. I bought an extra pair off Ebay because a bolt broke.   ‚Ä¢ Spare functional stock fuel injectors, airbox rubber boots/grommets ‚Ä¢ Spare new PIAA Fog Light wiring harnesses/relay switch/fuse (they sent me two for some reason)  Key Maintenance/Parts/Upgrades ‚Ä¢ 53K: New rear main seal, new clutch kit from Bosch, all fluids flushed (drives, brake fluid, oil, etc), new rear brake pads, new AGM battery ‚Ä¢ 62K: New iridium single electrode spark plugs (Densos) ‚Ä¢ 62K: New continental alternator belt ‚Ä¢ 62K: New metal head and rubber gaskets/o rings etc from Athena, new valve stem seals and collets, piston and compression chambers thoroughly cleaned of all carbon deposits, valve timing set, oil changed ‚Ä¢ 62K: New upgraded Bosch V14 fuel injectors (4 pintels instead of one) used on newer R1200 models. ‚Ä¢ 62K: New Air Filter ‚Ä¢ 63K: 600mile valve maintenance follow up. Slackened head bolts retightened, valve timing readjusted (new oil and oil filter 20W50 motorcycle oil), throttle bodies resynched. ‚Ä¢ 63K: New ABS mirrors, new PIAA fog light relay/fuse/wiring ‚Ä¢ 63K: New starter ‚Ä¢ 64k front brake pads replaced and fluids flushed   Other stuff that is helpful ‚Ä¢ Most of the bolts are 3,4, 6, 8, 10mm with a pitch of 1.25 if you need a handful ever from a hardware store ‚Ä¢ Euromotoelectrics.com have most if not all the parts you ever need and can ship to you within two days easily. They are amazing people through and through. Way cheaper than BMW, quality service, quality parts, BMW Tigard sucks miserably so do not go there. ‚Ä¢ Beamerboneyard.com ‚Ä¢ RealOEM.com if you need to cross reference parts or need schematics of anything on the bike ‚Ä¢ Youtube: Chris Harris. This guy is amazing, if you need any video guides on how to do pretty much any thing on the bike this guy has you covered. ‚Ä¢ Forums and communities of enthusiasts for guides and help on anything you need: Advrider.com, BMWspourttouring.com, UKgser.com, Prelicanparts.com  Anyways, if you have any other questions just ask. Best, Joseph  BMW, Touring, Dual-Sport, Adventure, Funduro, Enduro, Oilhead, Boxer, Classic, Shaft Drive, Paralever, Flat-Twin, Motorrad

Title: 2022 Honda Pioneer 1000 Trail SxS: Pioneer 1000
text: calcustompaso.com2022 Honda Pioneer 1000 Trail SxS: Pioneer 1000 - $20,099 + FeesCOMFORT3-PERSON CONTOURED BENCH SEAT: Tough, durable and built to enhance every driving experience ‚Äî yes, we‚Äôre talking about the seat. Contoured for three passengers, the center seat is positioned up and forward to maximize space and comfort, and the covering is designed to resist both the elements and heavy use.LCD INSTRUMENT DISPLAY: Completely redesigned for 2022, the instrument display is much easier to read, with big, bright new graphics. The display now includes a clutch indicator and a battery-voltage readout too, in addition to speed, fuel level, RPM, transmission mode, water temperature, trip information and more.REAR-VIEW MIRROR: All our new 2022 Pioneer 1000 models feature an integral rear-view mirror mounting bracket on the rollover protection structure. The mirror itself is standard equipment on the Pioneer 1000 Trail, and an available accessory on all other trims.SOPHISTICATED CHASSIS: Some of the most impressive Pioneer 1000 features are those you‚Äôll never see. In addition to the suspension and ground clearance, we rubber-mounted the engine and exhaust system to insulate the cabin against excessive vibration. So while you may not see this feature, it‚Äôs one you will definitely notice.TILT WHEEL: With a tilt steering wheel redesigned for 2022 to make getting in and out easier than ever, you‚Äôre ensured an even more comfortable driving experience. We‚Äôve given the wheel a wide range of adjustments for optimum customization and a new spring-loaded damper that makes tilting it a snap.COOLER CABIN: Our engineers have given the whole Pioneer 1000 lineup some big improvements when it comes to managing cabin heat. You‚Äôll ride cooler and be more comfortable in warm-weather conditions.ENGINEERINGi-4WD: The Pioneer 1000 Trail showcase our exclusive i-4WD system. Think ‚ÄúI‚Äù for ‚ÄúIntelligent,‚Äù because that‚Äôs exactly what it is. An industry-first brake-traction control system for side-by-sides, it simplifies operation, increases drivability and optimizes traction. Using proven, advanced technology from the Honda automotive division, you get the benefits associated with a locked front differential with none of the downsides. That means it maintains front-wheel traction even if one wheel wants to spin on ice or mud or if it‚Äôs in a hole. But at the same time, you get the lighter steering, better tracking at high speeds, tighter turning radius, and reduced kickback associated with unlocked front differentials.ADVANCED TRANSMISSION LOGIC: The brain of the DCT, Advanced Transmission Logic, senses how you drive and adapts. Relaxed drivers get earlier shifts for a quieter ride at lower engine speeds. Sportier drivers will hold each gear longer for higher RPM shifts. And when going downhill, you get true engine braking. Now that‚Äôs a smart transmission.REDESIGNED PARKING INTERLOCK: Even something like the parking brake is better on the 2022 Pioneer 1000. We‚Äôve taken the old three-cable design and replaced it with one push/pull cable that makes adjusting easier and cuts down on servicing.HANDLINGCHASSIS AND SUSPENSION: Prepare to go further than ever before. Our refined chassis enables you to tackle terrain others would shy away from, with larger tires, long-travel independent front and rear suspension and huge ground clearance. The rubber mounted engine and exhaust system insulates against excessive vibration.OTR DIRT MASTER: All our Pioneer 1000 models for 2022 feature high-performance OTR Dirt Master tires for excellent off-road traction and superior wear.THREE DIFFERENT WHEEL CHOICES: Our four Pioneer 1000 models come with three different wheel choices. The Pioneer 1000 Trail Edition gets 14-inch black aluminum wheels with contrast-cut highlights.EPS SYSTEM: This is something we‚Äôre really proud of. Honda pioneered (no pun intended) electric power steering on our side by sides, and now we‚Äôre making it better. Every 2022 Pioneer 1000 gets a new EPS system with a new, brushless motor integrated with the ECU. The return-to-center function makes it more intuitiv on straight trails, and the whole system feels more linear.INDEPENDENT FRONT AND REAR SUSPENSION: Dual A-arm suspension gives you 10.5 inches of travel in the front, and 10-inches of travel in the rear. Pair that with stellar ground clearance, and you maximize available traction and superior comfort maneuvering over terrain other side-by-sides would shy away from.PADDLE SHIFTING: Steering column-mounted paddle shifters add a serious dose of performance in every drive. In Manual mode, they let you shift without ever taking your hands off the wheel, and in Automatic mode, they let you override the current gear with a quick up or downshift, holding that gear for several seconds before returning to Automatic mode.TURF/2WD/4WD/DIFF LOCK: Don‚Äôt tear up sensitive surfaces. Select Turf Mode. Want to access as much traction as possible? Put it in 4WD. Need maximum power at all four wheels? Lock the front and rear differentials. And the best part is, you can do it all with a shift of a single lever.PERFORMANCEMORE POWERFUL 999cc TWIN-CYLINDER ENGINE: We‚Äôve boosted the engine power in our entire Pioneer 1000 lineup, especially in the midrange and top end. The improved acceleration and overall performance is noticeable, magnified by this year‚Äôs new lower gear ratios. Using the same Unicam¬Æ cylinder head design found in our motocross bikes, the class-leading 999cc liquid-cooled inline twin is more compact, and it still delivers the kind of horsepower and torque you‚Äôd expect from a flagship model.2500-POUND TOWING CAPACITY: Have a big load to haul? Great news for 2022‚Äîwe've increased the Pioneer 1000's towing capacity to 2500 pounds. So now instead of hopping on the tractor or taking out the truck, you can stay right in your side-by-side and tackle those bigger jobs with relative ease.BUILT IN THE U.S.A.: The Pioneer 1000 is purpose-built for the American market, right in America. Domestically and globally sourced parts are all assembled at our plant in Timmonsville, South Carolina, and once these side-by-sides roll off the line, they‚Äôre ready to explore every corner of the country.FULLY-AUTOMATIC SIX-SPEED DCT TRANSMISSION: Drive the way you want, with the industry‚Äôs first and only all gear six-speed Dual Clutch Transmission. Choose between manual mode or fully automatic. Plus, the addition of Sport Mode increases the fun, shifting at higher RPM for a spirited, full-performance driving experience.HIGH/LOW SUBTRANSMISSION: With a full 42-percent gear reduction between High and Low, you get the torque you need in all six gears. It comes in handy when driving over difficult terrain, scaling steep hills or towing heavy loads.GEAR RATIOS: For 2022, all Pioneer 1000 models get new gear ratios in the transmission, subtransmission, and final drive. They help improve your Pioneer‚Äôs versatility under all driving conditions.SAFETYSAFETY NETS: We‚Äôve upgraded the safety nets on all our Pioneer 1000 models to connect and disconnect more easily, just like on our Talon sport SxS models. We‚Äôve changed the mesh pattern too.DRIVER/PASSENGER PROTECTION: The Occupant Protection Structure uses large-diameter tubing, and meets ISO‚Äôs rollover protection standard. The hard doors and roll-up side nets help keep debris from entering the cabin, and auto-style three-point seatbelts are equipped with an emergency locking retractor mechanism, to help optimize passenger security. When you put this much safety first, fun is sure to follow.FOUR-WHEEL DISC BRAKES: The Pioneer‚Äôs uncompromising power helps take you further than ever before. The reliable disc brakes help you stop on a dime. Built to the same standard as you‚Äôd find in our autos, the four-wheel disc brakes minimize debris from building up, ensuring consistent performance, and giving you confidence on the trail.VERSATILITYNEW FOREST AND TRAIL MODELS: New for 2022, we‚Äôre happy to announce two new Pioneer 1000 models: our Trail and Forest versions. They‚Äôre loaded with factory-installed accessories and extras, like Warn winches, special wheels, cabin lighting, special paint and graphics, and much more.1000-POUND-CAPACITY TILT BED: There are a ton of reasons to buy a Pioneer 1000. Among them: the half-ton hauling capacity*. And when it comes to dumping, we‚Äôve made it easier than ever, with a hydraulic assist tilt bed lever that can be accessed from outside the vehicle, or right from the driver‚Äôs seat. *600-pound bed capacity for CA modelsMORE UNDERSEAT STORAGE: The Pioneer 1000‚Äôs underseat storage area is much improved for 2022. We‚Äôve made the opening larger, which makes getting objects in and out a lot easier.BIGGER CUPHOLDERS: You asked, we listened. The primary dash-mounted cupholders in our 2022 Pioneer 1000 models are upsized this year, and big enough to hold the most popular insulated tumblers. Plus, all Pioneer 1000 models also feature cup holders in every door. Designed to hold your water bottles securely, it‚Äôs a convenient touch everyone will appreciate.UNDER-DASH STORAGE: Standard equipment on the Pioneer 1000 Trail, and as an available accessory on the Pioneer 1000, this practical under-dash shelf keeps frequently used items right up front in the cab.WARN VRX 45 WINCH: This is a huge upgrade and standard equipment on our Pioneer 1000 Trail models. The winch is installed at the factory, and is built right into the Pioneer‚Äôs chassis, not added on as an accessory. With a 4500-pound capacity and spooled with steel cable, you‚Äôll be ready to pull your buddy out when he gets stuck!ACCESSORY SWITCH PANEL: Standard equipment on the 2022 Pioneer 1000 Trail, the switch panel has room for seven switches, letting you control things like a winch, accessory lights, and more. A fully integrated design, it sits in the center of the dashboard, underneath the other switches and controls.12-VOLT ACCESSORY SOCKET: The Pioneer 1000 Trail all feature a standard 12-volt power socket in the bed. Using a common ‚Äúcigarette-lighter‚Äù style of outlet, it‚Äôs perfect for powering things like a spotlight, work light, sprayer, air compressor, 110-volt inverter and more.INTERIOR LIGHT: Our new 2022 Pioneer 1000 Trail come with an interior light that lights up the floor area of the cabin., It‚Äôs convenient, and a big help illuminating the under-dash storage area so you can find your items in low-light conditions.ENGINE AIR INTAKE: To get the most out of your engine, you need the best air going into it. That‚Äôs why we positioned the air intake up high under the hood. Here is a glimpse at just the top ten uses of utility trailers:  1.Automobiles: From time to time it becomes necessary to haul an inoperable car or truck. Tow trucks are expensive, especially if the distance is great. A utility trailer is a great way to haul vehicles and a good investment if you need to do so regularly.  2.Boats: If you have a boat, you will need a utility trailer to get it to and from the water.  3.Lawn Care Equipment: If you live in a rural area, you may find that you need to haul your mowing equipment from one piece of your property to another. Packing equipment and loading it into a pickup truck bed can get old very quickly. A utility trailer will allow you to drive your equipment right up onto the trailer without the aid of ramps or two strong men.  4.Furniture: Moving furniture is a breeze with a utility trailer. Furniture dollies roll right up onto the trailer and you can haul more than you can with a pickup.  5.Building Supplies: Do you have projects that need to be done around the house? Pick up your own building supplies and save on delivery fees.  6.Bikes, Motorcycles, and ATVs: Recreational vehicles are best hauled on a utility trailer.  7.Livestock: An enclosed utility trailer is most often used to haul livestock.  8.Auction and Flea Markets: If you frequent auctions and flea markets, you will need the hauling capability to bring home your inexpensive and rare finds.  9.Appliances: Utility trailers are ideal for hauling appliances.  10.Debris and Trash: Loading trash in and out of your pickup bed can be cumbersome and clean up can be messy, but it would be worse to have to haul trash in your SUV. Clean up after a big job is a lot easier with a utility trailer.  As you can see, there are many reasons why an investment in a utility trailer is a smart move.
